node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.text:
WHERE ARCHITECTS LIVE | Adam Haddow
​.
@aboutsjb director Adam Haddow’s own home, which he shares with his husband Mike and dog Eric, occupies the top floor of a heritage-listed warehouse. ​
​.
​The home achieves an overwhelming sense of calm among its urban surroundings through a meticulous floor plan organised around outdoor connections and a garden overflowing with native Australian flora.
​.
​Read more about Adam's home on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @adamhaddow
​Photography @felix_forest and Matthew Densley
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/where-architects-live-adam-haddow/

node.text:
HOME TOUR Central Park Road Residence II
​.
​Stealthy sitting behind the silhouette of its remnant heritage home, Central Park Road Residence II emerges as the considered renovation and extension of the home’s previous self.
​.
@studiofour.net.au used materiality and a revised sense of spatial interactions to tie the eras together with a newfound purpose, expressed through a series of muted and textured tones.
​.
​See more of this heritage home extension and renovation on est – link in profile.
​.
​Design @studiofour.net.au
​Photography @shannonmcgrath
​Words @bronwynmarshall
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/central-park-road-residence-ii-studiofour/d

node.text:
ARCHITECTURE | Catalonian Farmhouse 
​.
​Dreaming of a Spanish farmhouse to escape? You’re not the only one. Catalan Painter Adalina Coromines, designer Joan Lao and their daughter and designer Africa Lao searched for five years to find their ideal rural Spanish farmhouse. Here, they wanted to closeness to nature and be more sustainable.
​.
​The family found their match in a 17th-century Catalan farmhouse on a 62-acre farm in the Baix Empordà region to revamp. It’s made entirely out of stone, with clay walls and floors and untreated wooden beams. The converted farmhouse now includes a studio space, gallery space and meeting rooms for the creative crew.
​.
​See this home in our 'Best of est | Spanish Rural Retreats' feature – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @joanlao_studio
​Photography @eugenipons
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/est-collection-spanish-rural-retreats/
